<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06048208 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06048208 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Steve Jobs  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  CHARITY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  IF YOU want to have a good time for a good cause, here's a list of upcomingsocial events benefiting Bay Area charities.;    (box) The Ladies of Charity'sannual Black and White Ball begins at 7:30 p.m. Saturday at the MediterraneanCenter, Hyatt San Jose, 1740 N. First St. The Lyra Tones will provide musicand the group will celebrate its 60th anniversary. Black tie is preferred andproceeds from the $87.50 tickets go to support the child care programs at St.Elizabeth's Day Home. Information and reservations: (408) 264-4188 or (408)265-2596.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Living  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  GALA BALL CELEBRATES LADIES OF CHARITY'S60TH ANNIVERSARY  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Revels With a Cause  </MEMO><TEXT>     (box) The fifth annual &quot; '50s-'60s Heart Hop&quot; benefiting the Santa ClaraCounty chapter of the American Heart Association begins at 7:30 p.m. Saturdayin the San Jose Convention Center, 150 W. San Carlos St. Sha-Boom will playrock 'n' roll. Tickets are $30 in advance and $35 at the door. Information andreservations: (408) 247-8555.;    (box) The Foster Grandparent Program hostsits 18th annual Recognition Day luncheon at 11:30 a.m. March 1 at Lou'sVillage, 1465 W. San Carlos St., San Jose. Tickets are $15. Information andreservations: (408) 280-5553.;    (box) A casino evening benefiting San JoseCivic Light Opera's conservatory and outreach programs begins at 6:30 p.m.March 1 at the Red Lion Hotel, 2050 Gateway Place, San Jose. The eveningincludes a buffet dinner, dancing, an auction and games. Tickets are $75.Information and reservations: (408) 251-7259.;    (box) Friends FightingCancer is sponsoring a &quot;Splish Splash Ball&quot; benefiting the American CancerSociety from 3 to 9 p.m. March 3 at Paradise Beach, 175 San Pedro Square, SanJose. Beach attire is requested and there will be hors d'oeuvres,entertainment, silent and live auctions and games. Tickets are $95.Information and reservations: (408) 287-5973.;    (box) The &quot;1991 SomethingO'Special&quot; benefit for the Giarretto Institute for treating abused childrenbegins at 7 p.m. March 16 at the Fairmont Hotel, 170 S. Market St., San Jose.Joanna Kerns of &quot;Growing Pains&quot; will be a special guest and the eveningincludes cocktails, dinner and dancing. Dress is black tie. Tickets are $160.Information and reservations: (408) 353-2337.;    (box) The fifth annualJunior Achievement Business Hall of Fame dinner is 6:30 p.m. March 20 at theFairmont Hotel, 170 S. Market St. San Jose. The evening salutes William R.Hewlett, David Packard, Steve Wozniak, Steve Jobs, Al Ruffo, Tom McEnery, JayPinson, Clifford Swenson, Eugene Kleiner and Phil Boyce. Tickets are $150 forthe dinner and $200 for both the dinner and a private reception honoring themen. Information and reservations: (408) 943-1930.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  -- Mary Gottschalk  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910217  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  February  </MONTH><PG.COL>  8L  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  442  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday February 17, 199100048208,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>